On Thursday, December 02, 2004, at 12:44PM, Jason Z Upper <jzupper(-at-)hotmail.com> wrote:

> I also have a vacuum 
>gauge installed.  It reads around 10" when first starting, but reads 15-18" 
>once the engine is warm.

I think that's too low for BTDC timing. MY engine reads 13" right after start. Climbs to 15" as the idle rpm is automatically increased during the warmup phase and then goes to 16-17" when normal.

I know you've looked for vacuum leaks..I would double check the valves.

